Despite his recent injury, Djokovic is preparing to compete in the tournament just weeks after his surgery. Djokovic has won Wimbledon six times and is hoping to add another title to his collection. Other articles highlight Djokovic's strong performance in his return match, where he defeated Vit Kopriva in the first round. Djokovic is set to face Andy Murray, who has also recently returned from injury, in the tournament. Djokovic remains optimistic about his chances of success at Wimbledon, stating that he is going "all in" and is "extremely glad" with the condition of his knee.

summary: The long-awaited sequel to the 2000 epic "Gladiator" has released its first official footage, giving fans a glimpse of the highly anticipated film. The sequel features an impressive cast, including Pedro Pascal as Lucius's mentor, while Denzel Washington reprises his role as the enigmatic Emperor Commodus. name: Aged care pay rise
summary:
**News Article Headline Summary**

The Australian government has delayed a pay increase for aged care workers due to funding concerns. However, the pay rise is expected next year, with staggered implementation for some workers. The pay increase is part of a larger wage outcome for aged care workers, including nurses and midwives, who are set to receive a 28.4% pay rise. Despite the pay increase, a recent report highlights that many aged care homes are still falling short of minimum care standards. In the UK, certain individuals will not receive the new increased state pension rates due to eligibility criteria. In contrast, Australian and Victorian nurses have overwhelmingly approved a new pay deal, leading to potential improvements in care for older Australians in aged care homes.
